                            <comment id="12935766" author="neilm" created="Thu, 25 Nov 2010 14:12:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a patch with a test case that constructs various java.lang.Strings, constructs COSStrings from them and reads back the Strings, the byte[] and the PDF String that is written at the back end.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14199892" author="jahewson" created="Thu, 6 Nov 2014 06:41:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We really need to fix this in 2.0&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14222446" author="lehmi" created="Sun, 23 Nov 2014 18:08:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;All linked issues are not related to a possible bug in COSString. They are all about adding non WinANSI encoded strings to a pdf, see &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-922&quot; title=&quot;True type PDFont subclass only supports WinAnsiEncoding (hardcoded!)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-922&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-922&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14222448" author="jira-bot" created="Sun, 23 Nov 2014 18:10:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1641237 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=lehmi&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;lehmi&quot;&gt;lehmi&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1641237&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1641237&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-904&quot; title=&quot;Potential issue with COSString and UTF-16-encoded Strings.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-904&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-904&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: added some more unicode test cases as proposed by NeilMcErlean&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14222451" author="lehmi" created="Sun, 23 Nov 2014 18:13:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The described issue doesn&apos;t exist anymore. Nevertheless I&apos;ve added the testcases include in the proposed patch to the trunk.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the contribution!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14222570" author="jahewson" created="Mon, 24 Nov 2014 01:25:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue still exists, COSString is still doing a &amp;gt; 255 check for UTF-16, and it is also using &quot;ISO-8859-1&quot; - an encoding that is never even used in PDF!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14307115" author="tilman" created="Thu, 5 Feb 2015 12:05:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jahewson&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jahewson&quot;&gt;jahewson&lt;/a&gt; Does it still exist now? &quot;ISO-8859-1&quot; and 255 are no longer in COSString after &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-1242&quot; title=&quot;Handle non ISO-8859-1 chars with drawString&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-1242&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-1242&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14307993" author="jahewson" created="Thu, 5 Feb 2015 21:02:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Nope, it&apos;s been fixed. We now check to see if each character is present in PDFDocEncoding and if not, the string is treated as UTF-16.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
